AER 1462257 is a spontaneous case, received on 15/Sep/2014 from a physician via health authority (Health 
Canada,MHPD, reference number: 541792, A1031792A) and concerns a 58 year old female patient who 
experienced aphasia, asthenia, cognitive disorder, infection, jc virus infection, leukopenia, lymphopenia, 
progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy and white matter lesion when treated with mycophenolate mofetil 
(Cellcept) and belimumab (Benlysta).
No medical history or past drugs were reported. Patient concurrent included hypertension. The patient's 
concomitant drugs included prednisone and hydroxychloroquine
On an unspecified date in Feb 2012, the patient started therapy with mycophenolate mofetil (route, form, dose and 
frequency not reported) for unknown indication. On 21/Feb/2013, patient started therapy with intravenous 
belimumab infusion 650 mg on 0, 2, 4 weeks and then every four weeks for systemic lupus erythematosus. On an 
unspecified date in Feb 2013, she received intravenous belimumab 680 mg infusion. Co manifestations of 
progressive multifocal leukoencephalopathy was brain virus, brain infection. Co manifestation of aphasia was 
dysphasia. Comanifestation of White matter lesion was white matter signal intensity abnormality. At end of May 
2013, she began to present with asthenia and cognitive problems. Workup revealed worsening of leucopenia. On 
13/Jun/2013, she received the most recent infusion of belimumab. It was reported that patient was still hospitalized 
